The paper describes an approach for unsupervised learning of a generic, distributed sentence encoder using an encoder-decoder model. The evaluation of the model is done on tasks related to natural language processing, such as semantic relatedness, paraphrase detection, and sentiment analysis. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses linear models for evaluation, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions image-sentence ranking, which could indicate a connection to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper uses a vocabulary expansion method, which could suggest a connection to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
